+`backoffLevel` controls the escalation window. It is incremented at **probe-dispatch time** — when `animate()` detects that the back-off window has elapsed and a probe session is about to be dispatched. It is NOT incremented on every rate-limit hit (in-flight concurrent sessions that complete rate-limited during an active window are coalesced). It resets to `0` after any non-rate-limited terminal (the session was `completed`, `failed`, `timeout`, or `cancelled`).
 
